Egypt Army Says Will Adhere to International Treaties (Text)

-- B y   I n a l   E r s a n
-- 
2011-02-12T18:31:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-12/egypt-army-says-will-adhere-to-international-treaties-text-.html
Below is a translation of Egypt’s
top military body’s fourth declaration read out on state
television today.
In the name of God the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful;
The fourth statement of the Supreme Council of the Armed Forces;
In view of the circumstances the country is going through and
the difficult times that have placed Egypt at a crossroad that
requires of us all to defend the stability of the nation, and
the achievements of the people; And as the current phase
requires a rearranging of the priorities of the state in a
manner that achieves the legitimate demands of the people and
delivers the nation from the current situation; The Supreme
Council of the Armed Forces, out of awareness that the rule of
law is not only a necessary guarantee for the freedom of
individuals, but also is the only legitimate basis of authority
and out of its determination and faith about all our national,
regional and international responsibilities, and out of
recognition of God’s rights and in the name of God, and with His
support, the Supreme Council of the Armed Forces announces the
following:
First: The Supreme Council of the Armed Forces is committed to
all that was stipulated in previous statements.
Second: The Supreme Council of the Armed Forces is confident in
the ability of Egypt’s people and institutions to get through
these current critical circumstances, and to that end, all
agencies of the state and the private sector must play their
previous patriotic role in driving the economy forward, and the
people must fulfill their responsibility toward that goal.
Third: The current government and governors shall continue to
run affairs until a new government is formed.
Fourth: The Supreme Council of the Armed Forces aspires to
guaranteeing a peaceful transition of authority within a free
and democratic system that allows for the assumption of power by
a civilian and elected authority to build a democratic and free
state.
Fifth: The Arab Republic of  Egypt  is committed to all regional
and international obligations and treaties.
Sixth: The Supreme Council of the Armed Forces calls on the
great people to cooperate with their fellow countrymen in the
civilian police force as amicability and cooperation must
prevail amongst all. It also calls on the civilian police force
to comply with to their motto “the police serve the people”.
God is the source of success.  To contact the reporter on this story:
